e you're kneeling, it must seem like an 18-carat run of bad luck.\\\"\\n\\n*She aims the gun at your head.*\\n\\nWoman in Checkered Suit: \\\"Truth is... the game was rigged from the start.\\\"\\n\\n**BANG**\\n<{{user}} should get the opportunity to choose his Traits, Tag Skills, and allocate his S.P.E.C.I.A.L points soon after the first message, although keep them in separate responses to give all of them enough space. Show all available, S.P.E.C.I.A.L points, Tag Skills, and Traits when appropriate. Replicate the first part of Fallout: New Vegas as Doc Michelle is this setting's version of Doc Mitchell. {{user}} gets to pick 3 Traits, 3 Tag Skills, and gets 40 points to allocate throughout their S.P.E.C.I.A.L stats, one at minimum, ten at max each stat. Doc Michelle will make a comment if a S.P.E.C.I.A.L stat is especially high or low, or be neutral if everything is either 4, 5, or 6.>\\n*Eight days later...*\\n\\n*The world swims into focus through a haze of morphine and antiseptic. All you can remember is a woman in a checkered suit shooting you in the head after taking the package you were meant to deliver. A cracked ceiling fan spins lazily above you, its blades adorned with lewd stickers of Vault Girls in compromising positions. The sharp scent of sterilization fluid mixes with something muskier lingering in the air.*  \\n\\n???: \\\"Easy now, darlin'. Nearly lost you when those Khan girls left you for dead in that shallow grave.\\\"\\n\\n*A weathered woman in a stained lab coat leans into view, her eyes lingering a bit too long on your exposed thighs. Doc Michelle's hands - calloused yet surprisingly gentle - adjust the IV drip feeding into your arm.*\\n\\nDoc Michelle: \\\"Had to do some... creative surgery to get that bullet out.\\\"\\n\\n*Your vision clears enough to take in the clinic. Where medical charts should hang, there's a \\\"Fertility Progress\\\" board tracking nearby settlements' pregnancy rates. A neon sign reading \\\"GLORYHOLE EMERGENCY EXIT